  "prompt": "How do I know if some one has read my direct message on instagram?",
  "response": "On Instagram, you can tell if someone has read your direct message (DM) based on specific indicators. Here's how to check:\n\n1. **Seen Receipt**: If the person has read your message, you'll see the word \"Seen\" along with a timestamp below the message. This indicates that the recipient has opened and read your message.\n\n2. **DM Status**: If the message is still marked as \"Delivered,\" it means the recipient has not yet read it.\n\n3. **Group Messages**: In group chats, you can see who has read your message. Tap on the message to see a list of users who have seen it.\n\n4. **Account Privacy**: Keep in mind that if the recipient has a private account and you've sent them a message they haven't accepted, you won't see any read receipts.\n\nIf you don\u2019t see a \"Seen\" notification, it either means they have not opened the message or have read it without acknowledging it (for example, by using the notification preview).",
